\intbl \ql \b Summary of Evaluator Report\b0 \line The evaluator indicated that most of the criteria \'28except for Criteria 6 and 8\'29 are in need of improvement.  The evaluator feels that such a course is necessary but evidence needs to be provided to indicate this. The film industry in South Africa is changing rapidly due to the introduction of High Definition Film Production\'2C the evaluator feels that any new accredited course should take into account the new jobs and skills needed to work in HD Film Production.\line \line The evaluator is also of the opinion that the programme has a very good combination and balance of theoretical and practical courses\'3B however\'2C it is difficult to see the vertical progression between each subsequent year. It is not adequately clear to the evaluator how the subjects and learning outcomes become more difficult as a student progresses through the degree.\line \line The evaluator states that the course does have work placement and an experiential learning module. However this is not present in the programme design. There is also an Experiential Learning document attached in criterion 6 but  there is no evidence that any of the students are going to be placed in the workplace to gain experiential learning.\line \line In terms of Criterion 2 the evaluator noted a number of inconsistencies between the Prospectus document and other information regarding the modules and courses discussed in the application.\line \line The evaluator believes that although staff members are qualified and there is a good combination of theoretical and practical lecturers\'2C the course coordinator may not have the necessary academic and teaching experience needed to oversee such a programme. In addition\'2C the application indicates that there will be only 1 full-time academic staff member while the others will be part-time. This is too few to effectively run such a course. The Bachelor of Film Production should have at least 2 full-time academic staff members.\line \line The information submitted refers to the acquisition of new equipment but there is insufficient detail to what this new equipment is. In the budget there is no reference to other sorts of equipment that is necessary to teach film production. For example jibs\'2C cranes\'2C dollies and any other new technologies.  It is important to the evaluation process to be able to see how many cameras\'2C lights etc SAE will buy to support their degree programme. What is the intended ratio of students to camera equipment\'2C lighting equipment etc\'3F\line \line The evaluator is satisfied with the infrastructure and library resources that SAE will provide. However\'2C the institution must make allowance for students to be able to work at the IZIKO library after 4pm. This is too early for a library that is servicing full-time degree students to close\line .\line The Directorate supports the recommendation for the provisional accreditation of the programme. \line \cell \pard 

